Conflicts: swaylock,
Description: Screen locker for Wayland compositors with authd support
 swaylock-authd is a derivative of swaylock, a screen locking utility for
 Wayland compositors implementing the ext-session-lock-v1 protocol.
 .
 This variant adds support for Ubuntu authd. When /run/authd.sock is present,
 authentication is driven through the GDM PAM extension JSON protocol
 (com.ubuntu.authd.gdm), presenting a multi-stage UI for broker selection,
 authentication mode selection, and challenge input including QR code layouts.
 .
 Features include colour and image backgrounds, scaling modes, PAM
 authentication, and authd multi-factor authentication support.
